    "title": "The Grasshopper — NZ forecast",
    "summary": "It was an absolute stunner down in the Southern Lakes on Thursday after the ski fields there received a couple of dustings from a pair of passing fronts on Wednesday and Wednesday night. Treble Cone scored a total of 6 cm of fresh powder, The Remarkables 5cm, Cardrona 4cm, and Coronet Peak 2cm, while the snow guns also got some run-time.",
