      "summary": ": Wednesday 15/7 Yesterday's snow has dried out nicely overnight. Cold overnight temps and low humidity have combined for some great grooming conditions. Snow on the lower mountain is firm. Today will start out clear but we are expecting a few snow flurries through the day. Little Bucks Park opens today with two jumps and 6 jibs. Get your laps in off the T-Bar! McDougall's, Learners, Whitestar and Valley View scheduled from 08:30 am. Captains and T-Bar to follow from 09:00 am. Soho OPEN (09:30am) recommended for advanced skiers only due to early season conditions and limited grooming. Willows closed for the day due to snow conditions (11am). Pines Shuttle buses will run as quickly as conditions allow. We may reach capacity on our shuttle service before 11:30am.",
