      "summary": ": 15 July Update Some great skiing/riding in upper part of the Saddle. Lots of nice turns to be enjoyed. Trickier down low as you hit the rain crust band so caution required and it's advanced skiers/riders only. Light is flat with a few snow flurries up high. This may clear out this afternoon. No wind to speak of and a nice cold but not freezing temperature. Summit slopes are on hold.",
